    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing around 20 species of trees and shrubs, all occurring in eastern North America and Mexico, growing 4 to 25 meters in height. Some species of Robinia are used as food by larvae of moths and butterflies.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
